body:
OK, I found the culprit. This works:

```
// DTOs

public class Foo
{
    public string Bar { get; set; }
    public int Baz { get; set; }
}

public class Qux
{
    public string Bar { get; }
    public int Baz { get; }

    public Qux(string bar)
            : this(42, bar)
    {
    }

    public Qux(int baz, string bar)
    {
        Bar = bar;
        Baz = baz;
    }
}

// in mapping profile
CreateMap<Foo, Qux>();

// main program
Mapper.AddProfile<MapperProfile>();

var foo = new Foo
{
    Bar = "bar",
    Baz = 17
};
var qux = Mapper.Map<Qux>(foo);
```

If I remove the `Baz` property from the `Foo` DTO, it doesn't work anymore, even though there is a constructor for `Qux` where all arguments can be satisified. This holds both for AutoMapper 4.1.1 and for 4.2.0-ci-1038.
